% Goal
Write the `pdd/agentic_common.py` module.

% Role & Scope
Shared infrastructure for agentic CLI invocations (Claude Code, Gemini/Antigravity, Codex, OpenCode). Provides reusable utilities for agent discovery, environment sanitization, logging, and subprocess orchestration. Acts as the low-level interface between PDD orchestrators and external agentic CLIs. It also exports a small set of git worktree helpers consumed by the change/bug/test orchestrators' clean-restart logic: `branch_checked_out_worktree(git_root, branch_name)` (returns the path of a live, non-prunable worktree that holds `branch_name`, parsing `git worktree list --porcelain`, else `None`), `clean_restart_fallback_branch(branch_name)` (a unique fallback branch name `<branch>-job-<slug>`, slug from `JOB_ID`/`PDD_JOB_ID` first-8-alphanumerics for stability across same-job retries, else a random token), and `current_worktree_branch(cwd)` (the worktree's current branch via `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD`, or `None` if detached). The Google provider supports two binaries during the migration ahead of Google's 2026-06-18 consumer-tier Gemini CLI cutoff: the legacy `gemini` CLI (`@google/gemini-cli`) and the Antigravity CLI (`agy`, installed via `curl ... install.sh`). The `agy` binary is preferred when available; the legacy `gemini` binary remains a safe rollback.

